Full Zod Verification Report — ShopKeet

✅ Jo Bilkul Sahi Hai
lib/validations/page.ts — EXCELLENT
Yeh file best-in-class hai pore codebase mein:

Puck JSON structure validate hoti hai (puckContentSchema)
512KB size limit enforce hoti hai validatePuckContent() mein
Slug reserved words check hai (api, admin, auth, etc.)
transform() se whitespace trim hoti hai
metaTitle 60 chars, metaDescription 160 chars — SEO correct limits
updatePageSchema mein slug uniqueness check bhi API route mein baad mein hota hai

lib/validations/store.ts — GOOD

50+ reserved subdomains block hain
Regex se attack vectors block hain
transform() se XSS characters <> strip hoti hain
validateSubdomain() aur validateStoreInput() helper functions exposed hain

lib/validations/auth.ts — GOOD

Password 12+ chars, uppercase, lowercase, number, special char — sab enforce hai
Email lowercase transform hai
Signup aur login alag schemas hain — correct

lib/validations/inventory.ts — GOOD

UUID validation on all foreign keys
createTransferSchema mein .refine() se source ≠ destination check hai
Sale schema mein price cents mein hai (int, min 0)

app/api/stores/[id]/products/route.ts — GOOD

createProductSchema.safeParse() properly use ho rahi hai
Rate limiting per store+user ID hai
Audit log + Inngest event fire ho raha hai
Cache invalidation pattern correct hai

app/api/storefront/[storeId]/products/[productId]/route.ts — GOOD

getAnonDatabase() correct use ho rahi hai (public endpoint)
Sirf safe fields exposed hain: id, name, price, image, images, description, slug
is_active = true aur deleted_at IS NULL dono filters hain
Store existence verify hoti hai pehle


🔴 CRITICAL — Zod Bilkul Nahi Hai
app/api/stores/[id]/popups/route.ts — POST
typescript// Abhi ka code:
const body = await req.json();
const { name } = body;
if (!name?.trim()) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: "Name is required" }, { status: 400 });
}
const sanitizedName = name.trim().replace(/[<>]/g, '').substring(0, 200);
Koi Zod nahi. Sirf name check ho raha hai. Baaki fields — trigger, conditions, content — blindly as any cast hokar DB mein ja rahi hain. Koi structure validation nahi, koi type check nahi, koi size limit nahi trigger object pe.
app/api/stores/[id]/templates/route.ts — POST
typescript// Abhi ka code:
const body = await req.json();
const { name, type } = body;
if (!name?.trim()) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Name is required" }, { status: 400 });
if (!type?.trim()) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Type is required" }, { status: 400 });
const sanitizedType = type.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9-]/g, '');
Same problem. type field sirf string sanitize ho raha hai — lekin koi enum check nahi ke valid values kya hain (header, footer, product-card). Merchant invalid type bhej sakta hai aur wo DB mein store ho jaayega. Phir template rendering break ho jaayegi silently.

